    {
      "type": "reference",
      "id": "6bf6cdc96e344e61",
      "site": "ward.asia.wiki.org",
      "slug": "ruby-sitemap-scrape",
      "title": "Ruby Sitemap Scrape",
      "text": "This is a rewrite of the first ruby scraper that saves text files useful for searching instead of whole sites in export format. It incrementally refetches pages that have changed based on dates in the sitemaps. [https://github.com/WardCunningham/search github]"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "23559e13c1f37028",
      "text": "The script loops over all pages of all known sites updating our records for any page that has changed."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "id": "f9d878938de70242",
      "text": "for all known sites\n  for each page in sitemap\n    if page changed since last visit\n      scrape fresh info for page"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "3166397a585ba1ea",
      "text": "Scrape looks for five different attributes on each page it visits. The values it finds are recorded in five different files. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "081f0e813ed91001",
      "text": "[[words file]]"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "8800058b58cd523d",
      "text": "[[links file]]"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "cd664058f27255b9",
      "text": "[[sites file]]"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "78ce5036e18c6fc1",
      "text": "[[slugs file]]"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "752c9b896e82b515",
      "text": "[[items file]]"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "2f4bf93402483afa",
      "text": "[[plugins file]]"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "83bef0e6129be035",
      "text": "We probe with http but now accept redirects so that https only sites can be scraped."
    }
  ],
